FROM: Ivan A. Schleder, CFP¬Æ, ChFC¬Æ, CRPC¬Æ, AWMA¬Æ
CONTENT: Luis, I‚Äôve encountered many people wondering if their survivors would be provided for should they pass away. While life insurance is probably the least ‚Äúfun‚Äù tool in the world of financial planning, it‚Äôs often the most important because that safety net can prevent the derailing of so many financial goals. Because of this, I wanted to summarize the broad categories of life insurance (specific policies will vary):  1.)  GROUP COVERAGE - Available through employer. Inexpensive. Automatic approval with no underwriting process. Terminates when employment ends.   2.)  TERM COVERAGE - Policy size and premium levels last for a specific period (10, 15, 20 years) then end. Underwriting process required. Not dependent on any employer.   3.)  CASH VALUE COVERAGE - Can be structured to potentially last for life. Underwriting process required. Not dependent on any employer. Builds cash value. May allow for premium contributions to be increased or decreased over the life of the policy. May allow the future death benefit to be used for present long-term care expenses.   Do you feel you have enough resources to provide for your survivors should you pass away?  (Before you purchase, be sure to ask your financial advisor about the life insurance policy‚Äôs features, benefits, risks and fees, and whether the life insurance is appropriate for you, based upon your financial situation and objectives. Variable life insurance is a complex investment vehicle that is subject to market risk, including the potential loss of principal invested.)

FROM: Ivan A. Schleder, CFP¬Æ, ChFC¬Æ, CRPC¬Æ, AWMA¬Æ
CONTENT: Luis, with the uncertainty in the US and global economy, now is an ideal time to re-target your investments. These seven essential investment strategies for smarter and more informed investing typically prove helpful:   1.)	THE POWER OF COMPOUNDING. Investing early and often helps remove emotion from investing and helps smooth the ups and downs of the market.   2.)	CONTROLLING EMOTIONS. Follow the investing strategy of ‚Äúbuy low, sell high‚Äù. Often people end up doing just the opposite. They buy stocks when they‚Äôre expensive and then sell them in a panic when prices drop.   3.)	DOLLAR-COST AVERAGING. Invest a set amount at specific intervals over time. That way, more shares are purchased when prices are low, and fewer shares are bought when prices are high.  4.)	DIVERSIFICATION. Take a broad view of your investments to reduce overall risk in any one area. Whether it‚Äôs tax diversification, investment approaches, or time diversification.  5.)	BE AWARE OF RISKS. Becoming educated and being realistic about common risks can help you make an unemotional assessment of just how much risk you‚Äôre willing to accept.  6.)	UNDERSTAND YOUR RISK TOLERANCE. Determining whether you‚Äôre a conservative, moderate or aggressive investor (or something in between) depends on what kind of gains or losses you‚Äôre willing to sustain in any given year.  7.)	REBALANCE. Your investments will shift over time, as some do well, and others don‚Äôt. Rebalancing hits the reset button, so the various pieces of your pie are brought back to the sizes you had at the start.  I advise clients in building and managing their investments using all these strategies. Which of the above do you feel you could improve upon?  (Diversification can help protect against certain investment risks but does not assure a profit or protect against loss.)

Hi Luis, The weather is now perfect in Korea ‚Äì how about you there?  The season is going smooth so far (6-0), and I still don‚Äôt think we will miss a single game till the end!   My internal disk failed without warning in my MacBook Pro a month ago. As a techie, I'm a little embarrassed to admit this, but it taught me some valuable lessons about SSDs. Here are a few tips to share with you:  ‚úÖ Avoid cheap ones. Even if the SSD is a brand name, the controller matters. For USB drives, you should avoid plastic ones, as they don't dissipate heat well.  ‚úÖ Run them periodically. Just leaving them sitting in a safe doesn't help at all. Run them periodically to keep them fresh and to maintain their electromagnetic resilience.  ‚úÖ Migrate to another drive after 5 years. SSDs have a limited lifespan, so it's best to migrate your data to a new drive after 5 years.  ‚úÖ Leave free space. Unlike HDDs, SSDs need free space to perform well and avoid failure. Aim for at least 10%, preferably 20%. Plus, data recovery is almost impossible for most cases.  ‚úÖ Back up, back up, back up! There is no perfect backup solution, but the 3-2-1 approach is a good place to start. This is what I suggest: 1Ô∏è‚É£ Long-term backup (3 to 6 months) to a disk image (Time Machine or Windows Image Backup)  2Ô∏è‚É£ Mid-term backup (1 to 3 months) to an external HDD (not SSD)  3Ô∏è‚É£ Short-term backup (1 week to 1 month) to a cloud storage service  I hope these tips help you to avoid the hassles that I went through. Drop me a line if you're unsure about anything.  Go Blue! Will

CONTENT: Luis,  Sent this to your email and wanted to send here as well. What I can‚Äôt see from your online profile and would be interested in discussing if you‚Äôre up for it, is how much cross-functional operational span of control you‚Äôve had beyond running product.  This exec will own their flagship Zola product, which Abacus acquired last year to be their core next gen practice management cloud platform. The GM will report to the CPXO Jennifer Sherman and will own the P&L, product vision, and go-to-market strategy. We‚Äôve worked with Jennifer on several projects and she is an absolute rock star ‚Äî highly accomplished, highest integrity, down-to-earth, good sense of humor.   Abacus was acquired by Thomas H Lee in 2021 with a plan to significantly increase market share and better introduce new products to existing install base. The company does $100M revenues today with over 12,000 law and accounting firms as clients.  This is flat out one of the best GM roles we've seen over the last few years. Abacus has a great executive team, investor backing, install base and set of assets ‚Äî and with Thomas H Lee‚Äôs backing they're now swinging for the fences. For an unstoppable builder type, this is the right opportunity to step in, up-level Zola‚Äôs product and GTM strategy, and play a key role in a huge success story at AbacusNext.  Let me know if any interest in discussing this more and getting to know each other. Happy to send along the JD as well. SUBJECT: Exciting Opportunity at Envoy
CONTENT: Envoy is seeking a dedicated Product Manager to join their team in San Francisco, CA! Envoy's workplace platform software has transformed how corporations welcome visitors, keep employees safe, book desks/conference rooms, and manage deliveries in over 20,000 locations. Companies like Slack, Pinterest, and Warby Parker us Envoy to create an unrivaled first impression and keep their offices running smoothly. Compensation consists of a competitive base salary, and equity package that depend on candidate experience. The role has incredible potential for professional growth and impact. SUBJECT: Remote Project Opportunity: Business Design/Business Model Consultant - Professional Services Organization
CONTENT: Luis,  I work for Business Talent Group, a subsidiary of Heidrick & Struggles. We are a marketplace that connects independent professionals with project-based work for our clients. If so, please apply with your resume, rate, and relevant experience here:  https://btg.secure.force.com/consultant/apex/ts2__jobdetails?jobId=a0o1W000007aqVl&tSource=a131W00000DG5r9QAD  Please note: To be considered for projects, you certify that you are not currently in a permanent role. This does not include contract roles or ownership of a consulting practice. CONVERSATION TITLE: VP Product, Incredible Health (a16z backed marketplace)
SUBJECT: VP Product, Incredible Health (a16z backed marketplace)
CONTENT: Hi Luis,   Hope this finds you well.   Reaching out as I'm working on a search: VP Product for Incredible Health: a 2 sided marketplace for healthcare professionals, starting with nurses.   IH is taking on a massive and outdated industry. Healthcare in the US is 3T annually, half of which is spent on labor. Nurse staffing alone is a 34B industry in the US while most facilities are understaffed in nurses. IH is well positioned to own the supply side: every nurse in the US. Already they are the #1 service in the country and >$38M ARR.   This is why Jeff Jordan at a16z led their series A in 2019 and joined the board. He's a leading expert in marketplace businesses, founder of OpenTable, on the boards of Airbnb, Instacart and Pinterest. He knows the incredible potential of a marketplace for healthcare workers and backed IH to win. They are profitable and don't need to raise again.   We're looking for a product and growth expert to help them mature the function and unlock supply side growth. The role leads a team of 5 (growing to 10) and reports to the CEO. Your background is a great fit.   I've attached a one pager with more about the company, team and investors. Would love to tell you more!   https://www.incrediblehealth.com/  https://www.inc.com/magazine/202011/teneshia-carr/iman-abuzeid-incredible-health-female-founders-2020.html  https://a16z.com/2019/11/28/nurses-healthcare-career/  Regards,  Hunter Moore Associate at Build Talent

Hi Luis!   Hope you're doing well.   I was sad to hear that you thought I was being withholding of information and resources, and you felt like I wasn't willing to let go of control of the team. If I made you feel that way I apologize, and it certainly wasn't my intentions. I wish you would've said something when you started feeling that way rather than me hearing about it after you left. I want to clarify because I was extremely excited for you to start as my boss as I really wanted a mentor and someone to learn about product from. I thought I made that pretty clear right from the start. I wouldn't have cared if you took the entire team because you were my boss and you had every right to do whatever you wanted.  I always treated you with respect, and if it ever felt like I was pushing back on any resources or asking you to reconsider something, it was to protect you from any backlash and to give you the honest feedback you requested. I thought we had a transparent enough relationship where I could be honest with you. Within a couple of weeks, I could tell you were on the radar for pulling a lot of time and resources from many places in the company, and people felt like they weren't able to work on the things that they were previously working on. That was why I gave you feedback on it. I didn't want the first time you were hearing it to be from someone else.   In fact, every time someone complained, I asked for patience as I knew the tough position you were in. It's a difficult job. Even when I was on vacation or over the weekends,¬† I still took time to answer your questions and jump on calls with you. I tried to include you on as many meetings as possible to the point where you sat in on almost all the meetings I was in. I wouldn't have done that if I wasn't trying to help you succeed at your job.  I really hope you can see that I wasn't your enemy at the company.  By the way, I noticed you left something I'm sure is of meaning to you from your daughter. It's a laminated paper tie. I can ship it to you if you give me your address! Let me know what you want me to do with it.  Best, Allen

SUBJECT: REMOTE Tech opportunity with FL based company
CONTENT: Hi I came across your profile and wanted to reach out to you about an opportunity I am recruiting for.  I have a wonderful client in FL- they are an established business that make healthy products for both pets and people. They have been around for several decades and boomed in 2020  They have warehousing/production/sales/distribution/e-commerce/ customer service elements to their business and the technology would need to encompass all these departments.   They are developing a new platform on SiteCore and they would like an in-house technology professional to join their team.   First and foremost- we are seeking a culture fit.   We are seeking someone inquisitive and can get to the root of the technology business needs across different departments. We are seeking someone humble, a visionary, and a team player who is a good communicator and craves feedback from end users.    We are seeking a "technology pioneer" who can ensure the company is using technology to their full advantage.  This is not a coding role and this is a role may actually morph and change and the title may not fit in a "box"  We are seeking someone who has architecture and development experience, someone who is consultative and can also communicate and translate between the "regular folks" and the "tech folks" and knows how to change their "language" depending on who they are talking to. We need someone who can understand, and communicate the needs back to the programmers and developers.   This role can become a bigger role if you like leadership- or it can be an individual contributor in a matrix-based org chart.  This role allows you to be nimble, creative, consultative and also be somewhat autonomous in developing tis technology to meet the business needs.   Please message me with your phone number and I can tell you more. Thanks-  Sheila LaFleur  Maritime Recruitment Leader

SUBJECT: Customer Experience Leader - Intuit
CONTENT: Luis,   I came across your profile and wanted to see if you were interested in a contract  role we are working on with Intuit. Let me know if you'd be interested. Must be Spanish speaking!   ‚Ä¢	REQUIRED: must be fluent in Spanish, written, verbal, able to understand feeling in a dialogue/customer empathy ‚Ä¢	Examples of questions the teams focus on: What is bad for the customer and what can we fix? What could drive a contact? How can we improve the user experience? How can be build a better experience for the customer? ‚Ä¢	Additionally, the team looks at themes from customer calls and text analytics and analyzes the data to build new processes/policies (i.e. updating the FAQ page or routing a Spanish speaking customer better on the phone, creating training for agents, optimizing routing, etc. ‚Ä¢	Potential day-to-day schedule: Cross functional team meeting in the morning (strategy team, product marketing/managers, finance partners, etc. involved), followed by another meeting with a care partner to brief them on how the team would support their strategy. Afternoon would consist of creative review and giving feedback if you see something confusing to a customer and then putting the journey for that customer on the page.  ‚Ä¢	Data side of the role will include weekly reporting from looking at call volume, understanding trends, and forecasting (partners would help with this component).  ‚Ä¢	Looking for someone who has customer empathy, is customer focused, team player, not afraid to speak up, assertive when needed, able to take data and create recommendations from it, a strategic thinker, is passionate about building product and not just the operational side of things, and open to a role that is fluid.   Jennifer Breadon jbreadon@cydio.com 619-573-4835

SUBJECT: Director of Product Management @ Alation
CONTENT: Hi Luis,   Your background looks interesting! I came across your profile while leading a search for a Director of Product Management.  Have you heard about Alation? We help companies leverage the full power of their corporate data to make better, faster business decisions. If data fascinates you, Alation is a fantastic place to work.  We‚Äôre looking for a highly strategic product leader to have complete ownership of major products, and also to define key priorities for our roadmap.   Would you be open to a conversation?   If you're interested, let‚Äôs find a time to talk soon, and see if there's a fit. Please send me your phone number and a few best times to reach you.   Thanks,  Margaret  ----- About Alation:   Our goal is to build a delightful and empowering experience for people who are asking really important questions, the answers to which are not on the internet, but rather are locked away in databases and spreadsheets. We're talking about people like executives at large companies, directors of universities, and leaders in government, as well as researchers and data scientists.  Today, the "interface" for getting answers to such questions is to write an email to an analyst, and wait weeks for a response. With Alation, users can find answers in milliseconds. And if the question requires human analysis, we empower the analyst to produce a report in minutes, not months.  We're a small team, already solving enormous data challenges, with big customers and big goals. We have Series B funding from investors including Andreessen Horowitz; our customers include eBay, Square, Albertsons, and many others.  Address: 805 Veterans Blvd #307, Redwood City, CA 94063  On LinkedIn: http://bit.ly/2jPqfLL   On Crunchbase: https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/alation  On Glassdoor: http://bit.ly/2jFigOK   Margaret Lebron Sourcer of Talent at Talentkast

SUBJECT: Approach for a Product Leader at Ladder - Consumer InsurTech
CONTENT: Hi Luis,   I hope this note finds you well. I work for Erevena (an executive search firm) and I am engaged on a search for a Product Leader to join the co-founders and other executives at Ladder.  Ladder are changing the way in which people think about life insurance and doing away with the old and broken nature of the industry. They are creating a product that is powered by AI/ML data modeling grounded by a customer experience that is as adaptable as life itself changes. Their view that life insurance should involve a more complete view of health encompassing both the mental and physical along with allowing for financial flexibility. CONTENT: Dear Luis,   I'm Roshana and I'm recruiting for a Product Manager role who is going to play a pivotal role at Willow Pumps. Hi Luis,   Your background looks interesting! I came across your profile while leading a search for a Director of Product Management.  Have you heard about Alation? We help companies leverage the full power of their corporate data to make better, faster business decisions. If data fascinates you, Alation is a fantastic place to work.  We‚Äôre looking for a highly strategic product leader to have complete ownership of major products, and also to define key priorities for our roadmap.   Would you be open to a conversation?   If you're interested, let‚Äôs find a time to talk soon, and see if there's a fit. Please send me your phone number and a few best times to reach you.   Thanks,  Sonam  ----- About Alation:   Our goal is to build a delightful and empowering experience for people who are asking really important questions, the answers to which are not on the internet, but rather are locked away in databases and spreadsheets. We're talking about people like executives at large companies, directors of universities, and leaders in government, as well as researchers and data scientists.  Today, the "interface" for getting answers to such questions is to write an email to an analyst, and wait weeks for a response. With Alation, users can find answers in milliseconds. And if the question requires human analysis, we empower the analyst to produce a report in minutes, not months.  We're a small team, already solving enormous data challenges, with big customers and big goals. We have Series B funding from investors including Andreessen Horowitz; our customers include eBay, Square, Albertsons, and many others.  Address: 805 Veterans Blvd #307, Redwood City, CA 94063  On LinkedIn: http://bit.ly/2jPqfLL   On Crunchbase: https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/alation  On Glassdoor: http://bit.ly/2jFigOK   Sonam Horstmann Recruiter at Talentkast

We all have more and more ways to share, yet sometimes the most meaningful moments - and the most meaningful people in our lives can slip through our fingers in a sea of more frivolous content. In an effort to create ways to truly commemorate what matters, Fuel (fuelyouth.com) has built a simple mobile tool that helps people express themselves by sourcing a new type of meaningful User Generated Content (UGC) to share with friends and family.   From wedding parties, baby showers, bar mitzvahs, to memorial services - there are moments that are made more special when we can capture the energy and words of our friends and family - and the heartfelt and interesting words but often, we are swept up in the moment. Capturing the legacy of loved ones matters, and giving a voice to the elderly and less digitally savvy is crucial to ensuring their important perspectives don‚Äôt go unexpressed and forever lost in time.   Our CEO, Mike Burns would love to provide a demonstration of the technology and see if there‚Äôs an opportunity to partner and create a powerful campaign that will let your audience use this technology to share deeper, more touching moments with the world and their loved ones.   Please let know when you‚Äôre available to connect.    Thank You,    Monica Mellado  mmellado@fuelyouth.com

SUBJECT: Qualtrics Career Opportunity
CONTENT: Hi Luis,   I recruit senior talent for Qualtrics, a multi-billion dollar unicorn backed by Sequoia, Accel, and Insight Venture Partners and the leader in customer insights. We are hiring a Senior Product Marketing Manager and think you would be an incredible fit for the role.   Here‚Äôs some quick background on Qualtrics and the opportunity:   Financially, Qualtrics is unique and stable. We have been cash flow positive since inception. In other words, we have a sound business that isn't reliant on marketing timing or investment to continue our rapid growth.     We started in a basement, bootstrapped for 10 years before finally accepting funding. Our $70M Series A was Sequoia and Accel‚Äôs largest joint investment to date. With our $150M Series B from Sequoia, Accel and Insight Venture Partners we became Accel‚Äôs largest investment since Facebook. We have over 8,500 enterprise clients in more than 90 countries. Qualtrics has 1,100 employees in offices around the world including Dallas, Provo, Seattle, Dublin, London, Sydney, and Melbourne.     I would love to schedule a call between you and Jay Choi, our head of product marketing and content, who can speak with you more about the opportunity. Would you be open to having a conversation? Please let me know.  Here is some recent news relating to Qualtrics:    http://www.businessinsider.com/enterprise-startups-to-bet-on-in-2016-2015-11 http://www.businessinsider.com/success-of-qualtrics-jared-smith-2016-4 http://fortune.com/2016/02/18/qualtrics-insights-platform/ http://fortune.com/2015/04/21/ryan-smith-changing-careers    Cheers,   Eliza Goldhardt elizag@qualtrics.com

SUBJECT: Ancestry and Genomics Market Research Study - $100 for your participation in a 20-30 minute phone call
CONTENT: Hi Luis,   I hope this note finds you well. I work at Deloitte Consulting and my team and I are conducting a market study on consumer ancestry and genomics products, specifically on direct to consumer products and services related to DNA tests for family history, traits, health and pharmacogenetics. I found your name on LinkedIn, and given your experience at Ancestry, I believe that you may have valuable expertise in this area.  Via this market study, we hope to understand the consumer ancestry and genomics market dynamics and trends, including key regulation affecting the industry and consumer preferences / adoption barriers. We would very much appreciate an opportunity to speak with you.    In exchange for your participation in a brief 20-30 minute informal phone call over the next week, we will gladly compensate you with a $100 honorarium as a gesture of our appreciation.  Your participation would be extremely helpful and completely confidential‚Äî your name, contact information, and employment information will not be included in any research and nothing will be personally attributable.  If you are willing to participate, could you please provide 1) your contact information (email/phone) and 2) a few times between now and the end of this week (Friday, June 10th) that would be convenient for you so that we can follow up to schedule a time?  Thanks in advance,   Jason Stanwood jstanwood@deloitte.com

SUBJECT: Quick Question
CONTENT: Hi Luis,    I came across your information on LinkedIn and was hoping to network with you. I imagine you get many messages on a daily basis so I hope you don't mind my reaching out to you! Hi Luis,   Thank you for accepting my invitation in LinkedIn and below is a new job role that you might be interested as it looks to be a good match to your profile let me know your view about it.   Below are the questions for you to answer if your interested and to advance in the selection process:   1. This role is a 40 hour per week, ongoing contract role. It will be set up as 6 month contracts. Are you able to go to work onsite in San Jose, CA?   2. This contract is as a w2 employee of Stage 4 Solutions, and you will be on contract to the client. Is that OK for you?   3. What is your hourly rate requirement for this project?   4. For which high tech B2B solutions have you developed messaging and positioning? What is the process you employ to develop messaging/positioning?   5. What is your experience with executive communications? Which executives have you supported and what content did you create for them?   6. Do you have experience in marketing education services?   7. Why did you leave your last position?   8. What are you looking to do in your next Career Role?     Let me introduce myself. I am Sendhil , a recruiter at Stage 4 Solutions, a marketing consulting and interim staffing company.  We are looking for a Product Marketing Manager ‚Äì Education Services will for a global enterprise high tech company. The Product Marketing Manager ‚Äì Education Services will be responsible for developing the messaging and positioning for all products and launches of the education services portfolio. Additionally, this role will involve working with the product marketing team to ensure aligned messaging and positioning in all the marketing content created. This role will also serve as the executive communications manager for the leader of the team.   This is a 40 hours per week; ongoing contract role (with 6 month contracts) onsite role at the client‚Äôs offices in San Jose, CA. This is a w-2 role as a Stage 4 Solutions‚Äô employee, health benefits provided.   Responsibilities:  ‚Ä¢ Work across the education services group and develop messaging and positioning for each solution within the portfolio and for each solution launch. Collaborate with Product Marketing Managers, Product Marketing and the marketing team.  ‚Ä¢ Develop messaging templates that will ensure consistency across the solution portfolio.  ‚Ä¢ Work with Product Marketing Managers to ensure that the messaging and positioning of the solution is accurately reflected in all related marketing content. Review content to ensure alignment.  ‚Ä¢ Work with group executive on executive communications needs ‚Äì creating presentations, articles, blogs, internal communications, etc.   Requirements:  ‚Ä¢ 5+ years relevant strategic messaging and executive communications experience in high tech B2B companies  ‚Ä¢ Solid track record in developing and executing messaging and positioning across a solutions portfolio  ‚Ä¢ Ability to collaborate effectively across a global organization  ‚Ä¢ Strong writing skills  ‚Ä¢ Bachelors degree, MBA preferred   Please submit your resume to our network at http://www.stage4solutions.com/careers.html (please apply to the Strategic Marketing Communications Manager (San Jose, CA) role).   Please feel free to forward this project opening to others who may be interested.   Thanks,      *****************************************************  Sendhil Kumar  Sr. Recruiter  Stage 4 Solutions, Inc.  Marketing Consulting & Interim Staffing  sendhil.kumar@stage4solutions.com  408-412-0445   www.stage4solutions.com  Join our network to hear about job openings:  http://www.stage4solutions.com/careers.html

Hey Luis - Here is a quick blurb on Entytle. Send me a blurb with relevant b/g and I will ping the CEO.     We've raised about $1.7MM from angels, and are working with a handful of beta customers to develop our SaaS offering. The best description of our business is the following write up:    Companies traditionally invest heavily in customer acquisition, but over time, do not get their fair share of follow-on sales opportunities.  A big deterrent is the relatively low ROI, mostly driven by the cost of lead identification and qualification. As a result, companies leave a lot of profitable revenue on the table because the pain points associated with identifying and following up on lower ASP sales.     Entytle, Inc. is a predictive data analytics company building software as a service (SaaS) to help B2B companies identify high probability follow-on sales opportunities.  We use analytics and machine learning applied to companies' enterprise-wide ‚Äúdark data‚Äù to identify these opportunities within their existing customer base.  The solution will help companies maximize the lifetime value of their customer base by selling additional products and services such as upgrades, replacements, cross-sales, consumable parts replacement, service contract renewal, etc.     We generate actionable leads and populate them back into the CRM of choice. Our value proposition is simple: dramatically reduce the time and cost it takes to generate a qualified lead, increase the size of the served available customer base, and improve conversion rate of leads into quotes and orders.

As a part of the Movoto team, you‚Äôll be collaborating with passionate people who love innovation, taking on challenges, and having fun along the way. We pride ourselves on an exciting, dynamic work culture driven by empowering team members to take bold risks.  As a Data Product Manager, your primary responsibility will be to create and efficiently maintain the most comprehensive, engaging, and trusted source of on-market and off-market properties in the real estate industry.  Responsibilities:  -Define and prioritize product development activities that achieves the #1 market position in the online real estate industry.  -Lead cross-functional team to meet and exceed quarterly property data comprehensiveness, accuracy, and user engagement metrics.  -Create technological systems and processes that accurately and efficiently acquire, update, and maintain on-market and off-market property data.

SUBJECT: Follow-up on Sr. Business Intelligence & Analytics Analyst at CBS News in San Francisco
CONTENT: Dear Luis,    I hadn't heard from you and just wanted to follow-up.  I work here at CBS Interactive and was doing some research when I came across your information.  I thought you may be someone who might be able to help me if I asked nicely :-)   We‚Äôre looking for a Sr. Business Intelligence & Analytics Analyst for our flagship brands (CBS.com, CBSNews.com, and CBS Audience Network), and I thought you might be interested in speaking to me about the role. It‚Äôs a new, truly amazing role based in San Francisco.  Are you interested?  If so, please forward a copy of your resume to me at augustine.bettencourt@cbsinteractive.com and I'll contact you to discuss. Please do send your resume directly to me at augustine.bettencourt@cbsinteractive.com, because Linked-in won't allow you to send attachments.   Thank you,  Augie Bettencourt  Sr Recruiter  CBS Interactive augustine.bettencourt@cbsinteractive.com  Job Description The business intelligence analyst is responsible for managing data and analysis requests from start to finish, including gathering data requirements, quality assurance of tagging, pulling data, analyzing it, compiling into reports, synthesizing recommendations from the data, and presenting results.  The analyst is required to partner closely with product management to ensure reporting needs are met.  This requires the analyst to be flexible to, intuitive about, and creative with the shifting needs of the business.  The analyst should also be proactive in identifying opportunities for analysis and optimization.  The business intelligence analyst will be required to provide analyses regarding programming, site performance, financial performance, and advertising effectiveness.  This position reports to the Senior Director of Analytics and Operations in the Business Intelligence group and works closely with other analysts, product managers, and engineers.

SUBJECT: Technical Program Management Opportunity! San Fran, CA
CONTENT: Hi Luis,    I hope you are doing well. I wanted to reach out and introduce myself as I came across your profile today during one of my searches. I wanted to make you aware of an opportunity in the area that I feel is worthy of your time- even If you're not looking at this time. That said, I did want to see if you might be willing to help me with one of my newer clients, as your security experience is so relevant to what they're looking for.    I'm currently working with a Comcast Ventures portfolio firm that just raised $8M during a Series A investment (they didn't necessarily need funds, and were already extremely profitable). They are a software product company that morphed from a consultancy to deliver security and big data analytics solutions to half of the Fortune 100. They made quite a few strategic connections early on and even though they are around 30 employees right now, are set to explode. They're looking for people that will be invested in growing their company.    One of the roles in particular I was wondering if you might be able to help me with is a Technical Program Manager position. They have an enterprise clientele base of 30+ Fortune 100 clients including JP Morgan, Accenture, and SunTrust to give you an example. This role, while a TPM, is much more than that. It's someone that needs to have the mentality of a partner of the firm. Their accounts are relatively large - $3M in scale, so there's quite a bit of meat on the bone.    We are looking for a TPM to oversee the enterprise implementations. You will be responsible for working with cross-functional teams to build out technically sound, value driven service offerings and You will be expected to simultaneously oversee multiple services projects.    Thank you so much in advance for your help! I'll be happy to speak further if this piques your interest.    Katie D. Smith  Katie@ehire.com  4049903308

I have agreed to help the founder/CEO of Shipwire, Damon Schechter, do some friends and family networking to try and locate a couple of world-class business strategists to join his Innovations Labs in Sunnyvale, CA.  His company got bought by Ingram Micro in December of last year, and Ingram has chartered Damon with building an incubation lab to generate new business ideas for Ingram to fold into their vast distribution network...or spin off as private entities.  With a $15M VC investment, Shipwire rose to the top of the competition, and made their market a two horse race (Shipwire versus Fulfillment by Amazon), ultimately leading to the acquisition of Shipwire by Ingram Micro, a Fortune 100 company. Doug. _____________________________  Doug Griffith Founder/Principal Management Architects, Inc. Wk. Hey Luis,    Sorry we never got a chance to catch up before Shally and I left for DC. Things just got incredibly hectic those last few weeks.     Yep, we've changed directions pretty dramatically on the startup. (Thanks for signing up for the beta, by the way.)    So here's the story: a few months ago, as we were still working on our digital publishing concept, we began working on a concept in the healthcare (or "healthtech", a now-popular term) space. Ultimately, we decided to put the publishing concept aside for now in favor of the healthcare concept.     This new concept is based on the idea that more and more people are trying to actively manage their own health, but many, if not most, people can't access and just don't understand their personal health data - at least not in a way that allows them to act upon this information and make better decisions about their health.     One major area where this personal health data is extremely confusing is medical tests, even seemingly basic ones. What we're trying to do with LuminateHealth is build a solution to make important indicators of overall health, such as the common blood test, more accessible and digestible for patients. Our initial approach is to provide clear graphics, visualizations, and explanations, so that patients can make better decisions about their health. And as part of this solution, we're also working to give patients direct access to their clinical data from various sources to allow them to manage, track, and selectively share it electronically.     Would love to get your thoughts on it too if you're around to chat in more detail this coming week. Let me know if you've got some time during the second half of the week. We can chat over the phone or via Skype.    How are things on your end? How's the family? And how are things at Accenture and with other projects you might be working on?    Let's catch up,    Sidd

SUBJECT: Starting the Dialogue
CONTENT: Hi Luis,    By way of introduction, my name is Amy DeCamp and I am a Principal with Baker Eliot. We are an executive search firm based in New York and we specialize in recruiting individuals into a variety of corporate leadership and private equity positions.  I am hoping to receive the benefit of your thoughts on a search we are currently conducting with a leading online retailer. I am sure you probably know our client quite well.  We are looking for an individual to step into our client‚Äôs growing eCommerce team and lead a series of high priority growth and operations initiatives on an international scale. In addition, this person will work side-by-side with the senior most business executives and will have a variety of career paths in the organization including general management positions.  I completely understand that you may not be actively looking to pursue new opportunities at this time, so beyond discussing this specific role, I would also enjoy learning more about your background and career interests so that we can keep you in mind for future opportunities. I know your time is quite valuable so I would be happy to schedule a time to speak when it is most convenient for you. I can be reached at (646) 757-2110 ext. 1005.  All the best, Amy

Thomas  O'Malley invited to join ThinkTank on Convetit :    Title    Tactical Consulting    Summary:    In this ThinkTank, I pose the question if consultants should be doing more to help their clients facilitate online engagement.  The combination of increased complexity, pace of change, and unprecedented transparency seems to have created a perfect storm of risk, even at the tactical decision level.  It would seem this is an opportunity for consulting companies to develop a range of more tactical services by leveraging online tools to give their clients the insights and confidence they need to pull a trigger on important tactical decisions. I'd like to get your thoughts on this.   Please visit http://www.convetit.com/tt/31/ for more information.

I am contacting you as a fellow group member of the Global Private Equity & Venture Capital. I am using the group open messaging system as I thought this topic may be of interest to you directly.    I wanted to share a new members‚Äô only portal powered by CrowdFundConnect for entrepreneurs and accredited investors within the health industry and invite you to our network.    Since 2005, our partner Healthios has participated in 65 transactions worth more than $9 billion of invested capital throughout the global healthcare industry as a FINRA/SEC registered broker dealer.    The market has changed over the past 15 years. A new law was enacted in 2012 to assist companies in gaining access to capital, the JOBS ACT. It is currently being implemented by the SEC with some sections already complete. Over time, this will open new avenues of funding for companies from seed to exit using either private equity or new ways to IPO at lower costs with less regulatory burden on the issuer.    Healthios is at the forefront of implementing new funding opportunities under the existing regulations and will quickly implement new funding options as the SEC completes the framework for a full suite of new options to allow companies to access equity investors.    We would love to have you as a participant in our members‚Äô only funding portal ‚Äì HealthiosXChange.com.  You can join here - www.healthiosxchange.com/signup and by using my referral code we will automatically connect there.    If you are a broker / dealer that would like to participate either as a sponsor for issuers or collect referral commissions for your investors please feel free to connect to me here on LinkedIn.    Sincerely,    Randy Shipley  www.linkedin.com/in/shipleyrandy  Crowdfundconnect.com

CONTENT: Hello all,   Been busy ramping in a new role. I am interested in the development of the idea and it'll be great to catch up.  Engels

Dear Friends,   In 2005 I started Bunchball, with the goal of making online experiences more engaging. That vision has evolved over the last 8 years into something much bigger than I ever could have imagined - the opportunity to use the big data that we're all generating every day as we interact with various systems as the catalyst to motivate, engage, and drive true loyalty among our customers, employees, and partners.   At Bunchball we've been living this vision since 2007, when we created the gamification industry, and we've spent the last six years perfecting the art and science of data-driven motivation. We believe that this is the future, and now we want to share it with the world.   In a few weeks, our book "Loyalty 3.0: How to Revolutionize Customer and Employee Engagement with Big Data and Gamification" comes out. We recently found out that if we can get 11,000 copies ordered before June 18th, the book will debut on the NY Times Bestseller list. Being on a list like the NY Times has become crucial in building momentum for books and their ideas, especially for first time authors like myself. We are actually well on our way with some large bulk purchases and it is within reach, but we need some help to get us the final mile.   The number one thing you can do to help right now is to pre-order the book (hardcover or ebook) from one of the following retailers:  - Amazon.com: http://bit.ly/Loyalty30A - BN.com: http://bit.ly/Loyalty30B  I would love your support, whether it is:  - Pre-ordering 1, 3, 10 or more books today. We're even offering bonus material if you order before June 18th: http://bit.ly/Loyalty30Bonus - Introducing me to someone that could blog about Loyalty 3.0 - Talking about the book on Facebook and Twitter (#gamification #loyalty30) - Introducing me to an employer that may be able to bulk buy books - Or by forwarding this message to ten people you know who are struggling with how to motivate their customers, partners, or employees, and asking them to pre-order. The book will actually really help.   Write me and let me know any other ideas you have! We believe that these ideas are critically important to the future of business, and we really need your help to get them out there.  Thank you for your friendship and support, rajat   btw - here are a few of the endorsements that people were kind enough to write about the book:   "Loyalty 3.0 is filled with major insights, and does a brilliant job of grounding the reader in fundamental concepts around motivation, big data, and gamification - building on these concepts through real-world case studies that bring the combinations to life ‚Äì and finishing with actionable ideas and next steps that enable you to test and operationalize these ideas in your own workplace and personal life." - Brad Smith, President & CEO, Intuit   "Relationships are the single greatest asset for all organizations. Relationships with customers, relationships with employees, relationships with partners. In Loyalty 3.0, Rajat Paharia reveals the new science of relationship building through big data and gamification." - Tim Brown, CEO, IDEO  "Rajat Paharia comprehensively explains how to create loyalty in the modern world full of data and connectivity. If you want to learn how to motivate and inspire employees, you must read this book.‚Äù - Dave Kerpen, New York Times bestselling author of Likeable Social Media and Likeable Business

All:    Please Excuse the mass mailing. But its for a great cause - a fundraiser to raise money to combat prostate and testicular Cancer.     If you have not heard of Movember, it is a campaign held only during the month of November of each year, where team members grow grandiose, flamboyant mustaches (not willy-nilly ones) to support men‚Äôs cancer causes (prostrate and testicular cancers - through the Prostrate Cancer Foundation and the Lance Armstrong Foundation).  It originated in Australia a number of years ago but has recently expanded to the US.  In 2011, the overall campaign raised $126 Million.  Here is the general web address: http://us.movember.com/  ut     You can donate either to me or the team (Pure Mustachio) in general here (http://us.movember.com/team/449205). Just push the donate link near the top of the page.    Thanks for your consideration    Kayo

SUBJECT: Senior Consultant for Branding and Internal Communications Consulting Firm
CONTENT: Hello Luis,     I am extremely impressed by your background and would love to connect with you to discuss opportunities. An innovative Consulting Firm focused on Strategic Communications and Branding is looking for an Senior Consultant to join their San Francisco team.The primary function of this role is to provide the client with outstanding design and delivery of change and communications initiatives.     Please let me know if you or someone you know might be interested in learning about this opening. I look forward to hearing from you.     Very best,     Ashley Dutra

Pleasure to meet you. My name is Ozzie DiVinere and I am the CEO/Founder of ForwardMetrics.     Earlier this year, ForwardMetrics launched a global publishing forum dedicated to providing professionals & organizations with inspiration for change and success in the form of articles from today's business leaders, strategic planners, coaches, consultants, and entrepreneurs.     This forum allows professionals to share articles on subjects they are passionate about in various channels, and organically grow their business via new exposure to our rapidly growing audience. New Contributors Include: Dr. Brene Brown, Dr. Tony Alessandra, Desi Williamson and Scott Klososky.     Based on your background, I would love to have you become a contributor on our site.     To begin submitting articles, please complete your Contributor Profile via http://forwardmetrics.com/signup/contributor and start submitting articles immediately for publication. These can be original articles or re-purposed blog posts you wish to share.     I encourage you to check out the site www.forwardmetrics.com and contact me with any questions you may have.     We look forward to sharing/promoting your contributions with our rapidly growing global audience.     Kind regards,   Ozzie      Ozzie Divinere   CEO, ForwardMetrics  e: ozzie@forwardmetrics.com   w: www.forwardmetrics.com     About ForwardMetrics   Our mission is to empower people and organizations to achieve success. We achieve this through an integration of inspiration, knowledge, a professional community of ForwardThinkers and the introduction of innovative tools.

SUBJECT: High Profile Career Opportunity
CONTENT: Luis,    My name is Irene Pappas and I am an executive recruiter with Adison and Partners.  Adison has been retained by Anheuser-Busch InBev (ABI) to identify a Digital Platform Manager based in their Palo Alto CA office.  This person will be a key member of ABI's newly expanded Digital Marketing Organization. The Digital Marketing team will consist of 12 ‚Äúsubject matter experts‚Äù within the Digital, Social and Mobile space who will develop and implement the overall digital roadmap for ABI.  The group will lead the Digital Strategy, Digital Execution and Digital Innovation for all brands within the US Business Unit and act as an external ambassador for ABI to the digital and marketing community while leading relationships with strategic digital partners including ‚Äì Yahoo, Facebook, Apple, etc. The Digital Platform Manager will be Responsible for implementing platforms and multi-brand key projects including:   ‚Ä¢Support the implementation of 3YP IBS/Marketing Platforms Roadmap ‚Ä¢Define and implement Website platform for all brands ‚Ä¢Define CRM platform for each brand and support implementation ‚Ä¢Work with Search agency to define and implement Search Strategy ‚Ä¢Ensure consistency in Mobile App developments, leveraging mobile framework  Would you have a minute to review the full position brief?  Please let me know the best email address  to forward you a detailed job spec.   If this is not for you, feel free to share this information with those in your network that might be a good fit.  Thanks, Irene

Hi Luis,    My name is Nathan Kievman and I just wanted to drop you a line, introduce myself, and see if you might want to connect further here on LinkedIn.     I am the CEO of LinkedStrategies.com, a boutique Social Media Lead Generation Agency; advising professionals, management consultants, venture firms and small to mid-sized businesses through innovative approaches on how to generate highly targeted relationships online which leads to fast, efficient, and highly profitable conversions in as little as 30 days for our clients. We do this by integrating proven techniques to grow our clients business which we have developed over the past two years serving clients such as Stephen M.R. Covey, Yanik Silver, John Assaraf, Marci Shimoff, as well as multi-national companies and many small businesses.     I am sharing this with you because I believe this program would benefit you a great deal and I would love to share with you an overview page about this service and when you are ready to move forward, fill out the information at the bottom of the page and we will schedule 15 minutes to finalize any details, answer any questions and get you started in generated leads for yourself. This program is called the LinkedIn Business Accelerator and you can get a bit more info at:    http://www.linkedstrategies.com/services/linkedin-business-accelerator/.    With extensive experience in generating successful campaigns for clients, we have distributed over one million communications to date with an average response rate of 6% and average appointment rate of 3% on our initial communication. Many clients have experienced between 50 to 300 pre-qualified and pre-screened prospect appointments in as little as 30 days.     Our services allow our clients and people like you to simply sit back and respond to inbound inquires. It‚Äôs fast, easy, and simple to get started. Our unique value is generating highly targeted conversations between our clients and their core target markets.       I understand we are all busy, so I do not wish to waste your time or my own. My reason for writing is to initiate an exchange over LinkedIn to see if there are any opportunities for us to work together, and if necessary, talk over the phone for a few minutes about working together as well.     Please send me your thoughts about that page I shared and if you are ready to do something together or would like to schedule a time with someone on my team to learn more, either send me a couple of times that could work for you here or fill out that form on the page and my team will get you on the phone with someone right away. For now, I or my assistant will follow up with a confirmation or alternative proposed times to talk.  In the meantime, feel free to send me an invitation to connect and I will gladly accept.    Wishing you well and have a great day!    Nate     _________________________________      Nathan Kievman  CEO, LinkedStrategies.com  (801) 953-3172 Mobile (text is ok)  http://www.linkedstrategies.com/

SUBJECT: Career and Visa Advice
CONTENT: Hello Jennifer,    I noticed your profile on LinkedIn and wanted to reach out.  I finished by MBA at Michigan a few year ago and began working as a management consultant here in the Bay Area.  I have recently started to look at making a switch and Visa looks like an interesting company.  I wonder if you would be available to chat for 15 - 20 minutes about your experiences both at Visa and more broadly in your career.     Any bit of advice would be very much appreciated.      My schedule is fairly flexible this week.  What would be a good time to chat?    I look forward to hearing from you.    Go Blue,    Luis Calderon

SUBJECT: Ross Social Venture Fund/Other Opportunities
CONTENT: Hi Luis,    My name is Jerel Ezell, and I am a U of M alum (class of 2008, Medical Anthropology). I graduated from Columbia's Mailman School of Public Health in 2010, and currently work in epidemiologic and population-based research at Henry Ford Hospital in Detroit. I've been reading quite a bit about the Ross Social Venture Fund, and think that the work I'm currently doing with a profit-driven clean technology org might dovetail well with your aspirations.     Outside of my epidemiologic work, I serve as Director with a Detroit-based urban agriculture company called Aquatic Productions and Consulting, LLC. We are a young, diverse group of entrepreneurial biochemists and public health scientists who have developed and patented an innovative, scalable system capable of mass producing fresh, organic fruits and vegetables using reclaimed freshwater from aquaculture systems or fish farms. The recycled water comes from adjoining fish culture tanks or ponds, and is filtered via the platform biotechnology, where no soil is required to grow value-added plant products such as tomatoes.    Our prototype, tentatively called the BioColumn, has been intimately engineered and refined over the past five years. Our technology is based on a novel, zero-discharge technology called aquaponics. We are interested in securing a strategic partnership with a local entities to support and fund the model. We have an executive summary and business plan available outlining the strong commercial potential of the BioColumn and horizontal growth opportunities for the organization. You can learn more about us at www.biocolumn.com.    Please feel free to contact me with questions or comments you may have. I look forward to hearing from you.    Best regards,    Jerel

SUBJECT: Slalom Consulting
CONTENT: Hi Luis-    I sincerely hope you do not mind me reaching out directly, but I did want to be proactive in my outreach to you. Based on the exceptional things we have heard in regards to you as a professional and your exemplary background, I had hoped that you may be open to engaging in an ‚Äúexploratory‚Äù phone conversation with me. I understand that you are hit up by recruiters left & right and I want to be mindful of that; however, my intention is not to sell you a bill of goods, but rather break the ice and get further acquainted.    I would like to understand what it is that drives you professionally and what your long-term aspirations are as it pertains to your career. In addition, I want to share the Slalom story and our goals moving forward in 2012. I truly hope you will take me up on my offer to chat and I look forward to hearing back from you in the coming days. Please know that I am willing to speak with you at your convenience, even if that means connecting after work hours. Have a nice afternoon.

CONTENT: Hey Vets!    I wanted to let you know about the latest and greatest Veteran-focused service that provides some of the things you have been looking for when you probably joined LinkedIn. Read the article from Lee Kelley and Join the movement!    by leekelley    We live in a world of social networking‚Ä¶ and considering the amount of people on Facebook, Linkedin, and now Google+, we must think it‚Äôs pretty cool.  Well, I recently learned about an exciting new community for vets. It‚Äôs called Armedzilla, and it seems to share elements from all of these social networks, while creating a unique experience for vets and organizations that provide services and support to vets.    In other words, they are all about vets, and we like that!    Here‚Äôs an excerpt from their site:    ArmedZilla is a social network. But it‚Äôs more than that. ArmedZilla is a movement around fundamentally changing our connection with America‚Äôs armed forces by creating a social platform that‚Äôs never existed before. It‚Äôs a never-ending conversation you control based on your own unique needs and interests that will help you gain direct access to the opportunities you deserve.  Specifically, ArmedZilla was designed to rally veterans, service members, families, friends and supporters around:    ‚Ä¢	finally bringing the military community together in one secure place;  ‚Ä¢	creating a support community to help ease transition from service into civilian life and ‚Äúmainstream‚Äù culture;  ‚Ä¢	using the power of social media to provide better access to veteran benefits, veteran service organizations (VSOs) and veteran-centric brands and other entities that support them;  ‚Ä¢	showing pride in and public recognition for military service contributions;  ‚Ä¢	connecting with people, issues and causes our community deems important.  ‚Äì  Okay, so I hope you can see why I like this site so much. But I haven‚Äôt even told you about my favorite part‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs called ‚ÄúKeypoints.‚Äù You can put in keypoints to create a visual history of your military experiences.    You can populate each keypoint with pictures and text, telling everyone your story from that time in your life. When they hover over the keypoints, they get a preview of what‚Äôs in there, or they can click on it to read more. This was so much fun, and I really enjoyed creating my own keypoints. It brought back a lot of good (and some not so good) memories.    Finally, Armedzilla has a growing number of ‚Äúchannels‚Äù from various non-profits and businesses geared toward the veteran community.    We‚Äôre always looking for great new tools and resources for vets, and I‚Äôd say keep your eyes on Armedzilla!    Join, it's Free! - https://armedzilla.com/register

SUBJECT: Advice for a stranger?
CONTENT: Hi Luis,    I found your profile through a friend on LinkedIn, and here I am sending you an email even though I am a complete stranger. Honestly, I just am looking for some advice from someone who does management consulting, and I don't personally know but one person in the field.     I actually just completed my first year in a PhD program in social psychology, and I've realized that this isn't what I want to be doing. Long story short, the job opportunities are extremely bleak and it's a long path to even be able to apply for the few opportunities. Also, I'm a very people-oriented person which can sometimes be disheartening when I spend 60 hours/week working on research in a basement with no people or windows.     I entered the field because I like statistics and psychology, but now I'm realizing that I've completely ignored my strength in actual human interactions (as in, not just looking at data points of various people). Anyway, I've been researching potential jobs, and management consulting seems to be of interest. The only problem is that I have no idea what it takes to enter a career in management consulting or where to start. I have a minor in business, but besides that I just have a bunch of psychology research experience to show for the past couple of years. I'm hardworking and will do what it takes to get there, but I honestly have no idea where to begin.    You seem to be successful in business, so alas, I turn to you for help. How did you get to be where you are, and where did you start? Is there any advice you could give me on management consulting?    I apologize for the random email from a stranger asking for advice, but if you have the time I would greatly appreciate any information you could provide.     All the best,    Marlea

SUBJECT: SuccessFactors/SAP Director of Customer Results San Mateo
CONTENT: Luis,    I‚Äôm reaching out both directly and in a networking capacity. I assumed that if you weren‚Äôt interested, then you most likely would know someone who is.  I‚Äôm currently recruiting for a Director of Customer Results to be based out of our corporate office in  San Mateo.  The Director of Customer Results is responsible for making sure SuccessFactors prospects and customers understand the value creating potential of our products. He or she is also responsible for measuring and helping improve that value through strong ROI and business cases.  Responsibilities   ‚Ä¢         Establish yourself as a go-to person for sales and sales managers, and a value-adding part of the day-to-day sales cycle ‚Ä¢         Interact with the primary buyers of SuccessFactors products, and convince them of our value proposition coach them to convince others of our value proposition ‚Ä¢         Drive programs to measure and improve the value that our customers realize ‚Ä¢         Develop our methodology and materials for value-based selling and results enhancement ‚Ä¢         Create new thought leadership collateral for marketing and sales campaigns  Ideal candidates will have at least 5+ years of successful Business Development with specific experience in developing of business cases for C-level audiences.  Any exposure to Software, Cloud computing and the Technology industry is favorable.   If you are interested please email me your resume directly to dconnor@successfactors.com or you can apply directly to the job at https://performancemanager4.successfactors.com/sfcareer/jobreqcareer?jobId=17536&company=sf&username=  If you aren‚Äôt interested please take a look at your network and see if you might know someone that would be a good fit for what we are looking for. Feel free to forward them this message or have them reach out to me directly.  Thank you for your time.  Dan Connor

TO: Talal Ali Ahmad,Art Ash,Mitra Ardron,Margarita Albors,LinkedIn Member,Monte Agro,Kathleen Archer,Bill Aube,Luis Calderon,Roxanne A.,Robert Bacon
CONTENT: Women are key assets in combating poverty, building their communities and creating new pathways to a more just and sustainable world. Philanthropists have been energized by stories and research that detail the profound impact of investing in women and girls. However, the world of financial services offers few vehicles that enable women and allies to move significant investment assets toward generating the Women Effect. Women Effect Investments (WEI) is a field-building initiative of Criterion Ventures that seeks to shape the financial markets to positively impact women and girls.    October‚Äôs Convergence gathering - http://hosted.verticalresponse.com/779479/d502c185f3/505769549/f932428228/ - confirmed our belief that the moment is now for gender lens investing.  We saw existing opportunities crystallize and new ones emerge as leaders engaged across the ecosystem.  The momentum was tangible ‚Äì and so was the sense that we are still early.  We emerged with a renewed commitment to continue to share stories, data and ideas.  We also found many shared priorities and tangible ways to work together to move investing with a gender lens forward ‚Äì and improve conditions for women and girls on a global scale.    Join us in our Gender Lens Investing Forum - http://www.linkedin.com/groups?gid=4095944&trk=myg_ugrp_ovr - a Linked In group, to continue the sharing, the collaboration, and the dialogue. This is a space for leaders interested in investing with a gender lens ‚Äì investors, entrepreneurs, philanthropists, development professionals, gender experts, and more.  The work of WEI is creating and strengthening both a set of engaged investors and a set of investment vehicles with a gender lens. This forum seeks to connect those who share these goals.

TO: Christopher Baum,LinkedIn Member,Margarita Myers Barry,LinkedIn Member,Massimo Baldini,Scott Arjun MSc, MBA,Bill Barclay,Luis Calderon,David Allen BS, CSM,Byron Bargas,David Albright
CONTENT: As the Great Recession slowly recedes, it's clear that we're not going back to the world of 2006. The world has changed, whether we like it or not. But where exactly are we going?     In his State of the Union Address tonight, President Obama spoke about reinventing America to compete in this new world, about investing in innovation to move our country and our economy forward.     Green entrepreneurs are bound to be a central part of this new innovation economy but not just because the government says so.     The future of business is green because it makes fundamental sense on every level.     The innovation economy is a green economy and entrepreneurs everywhere are already busy building it.     They are already hard at work developing clean fuels, clean energy, good food, and other innovations that are both good for business and good for the environment.     Green business is not just a luxury, and not just for polar bears.     Green business is good business, as the sustainability innovators like Gary Hirshberg at Stonyfield Farm, Janine Benyus at the Biomimicry Institute, and Ray Anderson at Interface have demonstrated over and over again.     By cutting waste, polluting less, and using nature as a business model the green business leaders have show that making money and making a difference can go hand in hand.     Some clear goals were laid out by the President, detailing the new direction we should move toward.     President Obama proposed that we place a million electric cars on the road by 2015, and that 80% of our power should be generated from clean sources by 2035. We could argue about the details, and I'm sure we will, but these sound like worthy goals.     What's more important than the numbers or the specific path that we take to reach them is the vision that we can work together to create an economy that is both strong and sustainable.     The world is loaded with problems that urgently need solutions and entrepreneurs across the country are already hard at work delivering these solutions, building great businesses along the way.     As the founder of Rent a Green Box, Spencer Brown has built a profitable business by supplying eco-friendly boxes made from recycled plastic for those who are moving.     Not only does his business save trees and reduce landfill waste, but it saves people money and makes moving day easier.     As the founder of the EcoHub in San Diego, Yeves Perez is building a space where green companies work and grow together, finding common ground in their shared vision of an economy that is both green and strong.     James Cass in Las Vegas has worked for years developing the Mojave Breeze as an innovative air cooling technology which will save people money as well as saving the planet.     Milan Stevanovich in Michigan is developing Local Power using technology developed by Hardin Geothermal to create local utilities that extract energy from the ground with geothermal heat pump systems, helping cities and power consumers as well as reducing our reliance on dirtier and more expensive forms of energy.     Change is inevitable, but we have the power to decide what kind of change we want to see. I hope we can agree that we all want to create a strong economy with good jobs and a better cleaner world for today and for the future.     If so, these fundamental connections should prove stronger and more resilient than the political differences that sometimes drive us apart. A move toward an innovative and greener economy that creates good jobs, strong businesses, and a healthier world sounds to me like the right direction for us all.     Glenn Croston is the author of 75 Green Businesses and Starting Green, and the founder of Starting Up Green, helping green businesses to tell their stories that change the world.

CONTENT: IDEO is opening an office in Mumbai in early 2011 and we're currently trying to fill a number of positions. Please share with friends, colleagues, classmates who might be interested in applying.     The initial hiring plan will include the following roles:     *   Human Factors  Specialist with a minimum of 3 years of experience   *   Interaction Designer with excellent visual design skills and a minimum of 3 years of experience   *   Communication Designer with a minimum of 3 years of experience   *   Industrial/Product Designer with a minimum of 3 years of experience   *   Business Development Lead with strong operational experience (see job description below) and a minimum of 5 years of experience    To read more about the positions and apply, please visit http://www.ideo.com/culture/careers/.     The Business Development position is not yet posted, so if you're interested in that one (description below), please email Natasha directly at ngibson@ideo.com    ________________________________    POSITION SPECIFICATIONS  BUSINESS DEVELOPMENT LEAD, IDEO INDIA    ORGANIZATION AND CULTURE      Founded in 1991, IDEO is an innovation and design firm that uses a human-centered, design-based approach to help organizations in the business, government, education, healthcare, and social sectors innovate and grow in three ways: Identify new ways to serve and support people by uncovering their latent needs, behaviors, and desires; Visualize new directions for companies and brands and design the offerings - products, services, spaces, media, and software - that bring innovation strategy to life; and Enable organizations to change their cultures and build the capabilities required to sustain innovation.    IDEO is known both externally and internally, for its unique culture.  As the company describes on its website: ‚Äú‚Ä¶our culture is 20+ years in the making. Compound that number by the hundreds of people who have contributed over the years and you get a special mix. Our values are part mad scientist (curious, experimental), bear-tamer (gutsy, agile), reiki master (hands-on, empathetic), and midnight tax accountant (optimistic, savvy). These qualities are reflected in the smallest details to the biggest endeavors, composing the medium in which great ideas are born and flourish‚Ä¶‚Äù  As a result of the IDEO‚Äôs unique culture, IDEO recognizes that one of the greatest challenges to bringing in strong leadership and team members is identifying people who can intuitively understand, integrate, and thrive within this unique professional community.    IDEO views people as its biggest asset.  The Firm describes the human cultural value driver as being ‚ÄúT-shaped‚Äù.  The vertical is a deep creative craft, a special talent or expert skill, the horizontal a curiosity to learn, an ability to understand and respect the knowledge of others and a collaborative and open mind.    IDEO thrives on peer relationships rather than hierarchies; on teams rather than lone thinkers.  It is fiercely protective of its open collaborative approach and believes it is the key enabler for the firm to deliver innovative, groundbreaking work.    At present, IDEO has just over 520 employees worldwide situated in 8 offices globally. IDEO is opening their new office in Mumbai, India in 2011. They are looking to hire talented and passionate designers to work on a range of projects in corporate, social and public sectors. Candidates will come from various fields and will include disciplines such as industrial and product design, interaction design, human factors, business design, communication design, service systems, environments design and more. We are looking to hire 6-8 people between June and December 2010. These people will begin their IDEO career in one of our global locations (US, UK or Shanghai) for a period of approximately 3 months before joining the IDEO-India team in Mumbai.    POSITION SUMMARY      The Business Development Lead will support the efforts of the organization in India, and by extension, Asia-Pacific, to drive the development, client relationship, and project scoping that ‚Äúmake sense‚Äù for the IDEO to take on.  This entails understanding IDEO‚Äôs ‚Äúsweet spot‚Äù in terms of leveraging its greatest assets, while also understanding the commercial dynamics that enable projects to meet both revenue and profitability targets.      MAJOR RESPONSIBILITIES    ¬∑      Serves as a contributing member of IDEO‚Äôs global business development team.    ‚Ä¢      Collaborate with location leadership team and the design community to develop a compelling offer of IDEO‚Äôs business value to new clients through their specific area of need.    ‚Ä¢      Build strong and sustainable relationships with clients.    ‚Ä¢      Find and realize new business opportunities for IDEO within the client organization.    ‚Ä¢      Understand IDEO‚Äôs positioning and specific needs within their organization.    ‚Ä¢      Understand IDEO‚Äôs organizational set up for implementation, and how it impacts the project and the Firm.    ‚Ä¢      Manage client expectations of the project content as it evolves.    ‚Ä¢      Scope project work tasks, timelines and budgets in collaboration with representatives of the various IDEO disciplines.      KEY SELECTION CRITERIA    ¬∑      Excellent verbal/written communication skills.    ‚Ä¢      Fluency in English and Hindi    ‚Ä¢      A true ‚Äúcustomer service‚Äù attitude.    ‚Ä¢      Exemplary time management and organizational skills.    ‚Ä¢      Experience in navigating Indian business development with entrepreneurial/creative service consultancy or managing a key account.    ‚Ä¢      University graduate in business, design, or related discipline.    ‚Ä¢      A minimum of five years proven experience in highly innovative and international business environments.    ‚Ä¢      Strong financial analysis, negotiation, and organizational skills.      IDEAL EXPERIENCE    ¬∑     Ideal Industry: Marketing oriented, branding, consumer facing industry    ¬∑      Current Company: Highly international and innovative product or service company    ¬∑     Current Position: Depending on the organization, could be Business Development Director, Client Relationship Manager, Product Development Director, Product Marketing Director, Consultant, Designer, or Strategic Planner, amongst other functions

CONTENT: I recently asked on linkedIn the following question to a group of IT professionals:  ‚ÄúDo you believe that UML models can effectively capture a Business Architecture and be easily understood by Business stakeholders? Which UML models have you found to be more easily understood by Business Stakeholders?‚Äù  The UML Models and their preferred audiences cited by the respondents are:  -Activity Diagram [Dynamic]:Developers, Business Analysts  -Use Case Diagrams [Dynamic]: Business Analysts  -State Diagram [Dynamic]: Developers -Sequence Diagram [Dynamic]: Architects -Class Diagram [Static]: Developers -Component Diagram [Static]:Architects -Package Diagram [Static]: Architects,   At the heart of the two questions is a need for communication among various stakeholders involved in a System Development effort that potentially hosts significant Information System components.   Within the broader scope of Enterprise Architecture, two main domains are frequently outlined: the Business Architecture and the Technology Architecture (OMG SOA Consortium EA2010 Working Group, 2010). Ideally, the Business Architecture should host a coherent collection of business processes, practices, business motivations, operating models, capabilities, value chains, and organizational models ‚Äì to list a few.  Ultimately, the Technology Architecture is a faithful instantiation of the Business Architecture. Technology Architecture gives substance to Business Architecture through various engineering artifacts that usually include significant Information Technology such as: Software Programs, Hardware Systems and Network Infrastructures.  These two broad Architectural domains (Business and Technology) respectively host two distinct groups of stakeholders: Business people and Technology people. These two groups of stakeholders traditionally speak and  respond to different languages that are determined by the nature of the artifacts they own and the activities they perform in their respective lines of duties.  Given the context previously outlined, the following issues and comments surfaced from the various responses I received:   -How can we bring business and technology stakeholders closer? -Conveying Information Effectively: what are the characteristics? -Just good enough modeling: who draws the line? -How easy is UML to learn by which stakeholder? -How often is UML style properly used? -BPMN vs UML -UML vs Agile/XP -UML vs Ubiquitous language  Feel free to comment on any item in the above list!  Didier Koffi

We are not only cheaper then every website who usually charge a commision and a listing fee but are more convenient way of buying and selling. We offer 1 year memberships which in return you can buy and sell as many times for a 20-30$ account. Buying is always free and if you dont want to buy a membership our 2-3 dollar listings fees are still cheaper then every other website. Why should you have to go to one website and be allowed to buy and sell and have to go to another website to buy authentic products. Why search around a million different websites when you can find over 200 brand names in one store. Allin1auctions.com not only provides these services but also lets you sell locally within you own city or town for free. It is the first website that actually gives back to its users. Allin1auctions.com thinks that the most ultimate customer service you can give is by giving back to your customers. Allin1auctions offers people rewards for helping making the company successful unlike other companies who make billions Allin1auctions.com thinks that if there making billions in sales a year and making millions more on membership fees why shouldnt the user get some of the profits. We want to give the users something back something that will also motivate them to help out the company but most important themselves. We offer a reward system when you sign up buy list or refer your friends buy earning points and winning prizes which no other website does. We offer contest for the highest Seller. We offer help and innitiatives for those who need it. We offer free shipping on all products baught on our online store. We offer 24/7 support. We offer the website to every single country with many different languages. We plan on getting 2 million users by 2010 and 100 million in sales of our online store within the year.  year 1 2010 2 million users 100 million in sales of online store  year 2 2011 5 million users 250 million in sales of online store  year 3 2012 8 million users 400 million in sales of onlinse store.  Allin1auctions.com's Ceo Bikram Perhar has many ideas which are highly original and plans to expand his company and take it to the next level with the year.
