Dear friends, cheerleaders, supporters, partners, clients and fans of whichbox‚Ñ¢,  I wanted to share some great news with you!  2010 started with a big bang for WhichBox Media - the first 2 weeks where a whirlwind of press releases, launch of our new company site and ...  THE BIG NEWS: Last week, WhichBox Media was chosen by AlwaysOn as one of the "OnMedia Top 100" winners. "Inclusion in the OnMedia 100 signifies leadership amongst its peers and game-changing approaches and technologies likely to disrupt existing markets and entrenched players. WhichBox Media was specially selected by the AlwaysOn editorial team and industry experts spanning the globe based on a set of five criteria: innovation, market potential, commercialization, stakeholder value, and media buzz." (see the complete press release below).  You can also read it here: http://whichboxmedia.com/press  This is a great honor for us. We did not nominate ourselves, are only one of 2 companies from Texas - and, from what we know, are the only company that has not received, yet, any substantial VC funding - but has gotten here on a lot of its own "steam".  And: stay tuned. There are some more great things in store for WhichBox Media.   Also: Check out our NEW WhichBox Media site here: http://www.whichboxmedia.com/  Great information on some of the things our platform does: http://www.whichboxmedia.com/about-whichbox A breakdown of all the programs we currently offer for publishers: http://www.whichboxmedia.com/publishing-programs-amp-services Information on how brands can leverage the whichbox‚Ñ¢ platform: http://www.whichboxmedia.com/brand-amp-advertiser-programs-amp-services  Before I forget: I'll be in NY from January 31 through February 7. We will receive our award on February 1 and I'll be on stage on February 2 in a CEO showcase. If there is anybody you think I should meet, connect with, talk to etc. - please let me know.  Cheers, and thank you all so much for your support, feedback, great advise, cheers and input: it keeps us going and connected to the "real" world - but it also helps us to succeed.  I really appreciate it!  Bettina  P.S. I apologize if some of you are receiving this message twice - since you are both in my personal address book and my LinkedIn network. I'll make it up to you :-) ______________________   WhichBox Media Selected by AlwaysOn as an OnMedia Top 100 Winner  Recognized for creating new opportunities in marketing, branding, advertising, and publishing.   Dallas, TX, January 14, 2010 ‚Äì WhichBox Media, an online publishing and Software as a Service provider, today announced, that it has been chosen by AlwaysOn as one of the "OnMedia Top 100" winners. Inclusion in the OnMedia 100 signifies leadership amongst its peers and game-changing approaches and technologies likely to disrupt existing markets and entrenched players. WhichBox Media was specially selected by the AlwaysOn editorial team and industry experts spanning the globe based on a set of five criteria: innovation, market potential, commercialization, stakeholder value, and media buzz.  The OnMedia 100 winners were selected from among hundreds of other technology companies nominated by investors, bankers, journalists and industry insiders. The AlwaysOn editorial team conducted a rigorous three-month selection process to finalize the 2010 list.  WhichBox Media is redefining content creation, publishing, discovery, distribution and monetization, freeing content, users, and publishers from the limitations imposed by today‚Äôs tools and content delivery concepts. With its Whichbox(tm) platform WhichBox Media is offering a game changing solution for embattled content owners to refocus on audience growth, user experiences, meaningful connections, content creation and, most importantly, monetization.  Bettina Bennett, CEO of WhichBox Media commented, "When you live on the edge of innovation and change, it's cool when your peers notice! We're excited to be recognized by AlwaysOn and OnMedia as being among the most disruptive, innovative and promising companies that are revolutionizing online media."  WhichBox Media and the OnMedia Top 100 Companies will be honored at the AlwaysOn's OnMedia NYC event on February 1st, at the Mandarin Oriental Hotel in New York City and will be featured as part of CEO presentations and high-level debates on which forces are disrupting user behavior and creating new opportunities in the marketing, branding, advertising, and public relations industries during the two-and-a-half-day event.  "Our view is that we are still moving up a very steep Internet innovation curve, which means the media world will continue to be radicalized" said Tony Perkins, founder and CEO of AlwaysOn. "We congratulate the OnMedia 100 winners for their success in introducing the tools, services, and platforms that continue to disrupt the old ways of Madison Avenue for the benefit of marketers and content consumers alike."  About WhichBox Media By publishers, for publishers, WhichBox Media is Software as a Service (SaaS) online publishing technology company. The whichbox‚Ñ¢ online publishing platform and services combine contextual relevancy driven, content focused, all-media technology with products for large and small online publishers and media companies. whichbox‚Ñ¢ scales to include entry-level options as well as fully branded, custom vertical, ‚Äúbox‚Äù publications in the whichbox‚Ñ¢ Network. Solutions are also available for content owners who want a dedicated ‚Äúwalled garden.‚Äù Brands work with whichbox‚Ñ¢ to easily build case studies, test sites, microsites, custom content and brand solutions.   Patrick Seaman, Chief Publisher & New Media Vanguard WhichBox Media http://www.whichboxmedia.com [1] http://www.whichbox.com [2] publisher@whichboxmedia.com Office: 214.350.6649 Fax: 214.350.6320  About AlwaysOn AlwaysOn is the leading business media brand networking the Global Silicon Valley. AlwaysOn helped ignite the social media revolution in early 2003 when it launched the AlwaysOn network (alwayson.goingon.com). In 2004, it became the first media brand to socially network its online readers and event attendees. AlwaysOn‚Äôs preeminent executive event series includes the Summit at Stanford, OnMedia, OnHollywood, OnDC, OnDemand, Venture Summit Silicon Valley, Venture Summit East, GoingGreen, GoingGreen East, and GoingGreen Europe. CONTENT: Traveling for work certainly takes away from most of the fun.  However, it's sort of nice to enjoy a descent hotel on an expense account (even if it's just hotel to office and back).    Must be nice to get back to town.  Every time I travel abroad, I find myself so graciously happy to be landing in San Diego.    Wow, setting up a VC fund!  Sounds like exciting work.    Recently, I've started to think that the next movement for a lot of the big technology companies is to farm out a lot of the R&D out to minor league type startups (instead of internally grow them) and then bring them in when they are successful.  Any truth in that?    Feel free to reach me on my cell phone at +1(703)786-7899 at any time.    At the risk of coming across as to eager, did you have any specific times in mind?  I want to make sure that my schedule is open.     I look forward to speaking with you.     Cheers,    Luis C.
